I'm walking through the clouded streets, with a cutter before my eyes.
I hear my heart like it beats, like the wing flap in the skies.
La la la la la, la la la la la.
La la la la la, la la la la la.
There is a lightning breaking up through the thick red clouds.
Behind an eagle dressing up fantastic feathers and he shouts.
Come and follow me through the time walls.
You will come and see the mirror of your call.
I'm jumping through the clouded twilight, and suddenly lose all my senses.
Waking up in a large hall, my mind without defenses.
La la la la la, la la la la la.
La la la la la, la la la la la.
All my thinking and hopes, I see them in front of me.
I feel a motion beginning to drop, I see another world in change with me.
Come and follow me through the time walls.
You will come and see the mirror of your call.
La la la la la, la la la la la.
I'm standing on the hilltop, the holds of this past and future free.
No constraints, no doctor, only love, it is diffused over here.
Come and follow me through the time walls.
You will come and see the mirror of your call.
